<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id14a98cbe-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d" identifier="/us/usc/t21/s847"><num value="847">§ 847.</num><heading> Additional penalties</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any penalty imposed for violation of this subchapter shall be in addition to, and not in lieu of, any civil or administrative penalty or sanction authorized by law.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id14a98cbf-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d">(<ref href="/us/pl/91/513/tII/s407">Pub. L. 91–513, title II, § 407</ref>, <date date="1970-10-27">Oct. 27, 1970</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/84/1265">84 Stat. 1265</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id14a98cc0-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id14a98cc1-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="id14a98cc2-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective on first day of seventh calendar month that begins after <date date="1970-10-26">Oct. 26, 1970</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/91/513/s704">section 704 of Pub. L. 91–513</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t21/s801">section 801 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
